National Security Advisor Susan E. Rice met with Indian National Security Advisor Shivshankar Menon to discuss the U.S.-India strategic partnership. They talked about expanding and strengthening their bilateral relationship, including economic and commercial ties. They also discussed enhancing security cooperation, progress on civil nuclear and clean energy cooperation, and collaborating on climate change. They also discussed India's support for a stable and prosperous Afghanistan. Ambassador Rice mentioned that President Obama was looking forward to welcoming Prime Minister Singh to the White House on September 27th, which will highlight India's role in regional security and provide an opportunity for the two leaders to enhance trade, investment, and development cooperation between the two countries.